As a member of the Business Development Department of HLG Vietnam, your main duties will be:
- Invite potential clients to the firm for further consultation about various immigration programs;
- Source, screen, and develop a pipeline of potential clients through different activities (cold calling, networking events, agents/referrers, personal relationships, etc.);
- Follow up with potential clients in order to close deals. After closing deals, keep taking care of them by coordinating with the involved departments of the Company;
- Support the Marketing team with event coordination and client invitation;
- Be responsible for personal KPI and targets;
- Participate in Company’s general activities such as seminars, events, training sessions, etc.;
- Other responsibilities as assigned.

Job Requirements:
- Vietnamese national;
- Gender: male or female;
- Educational level: Bachelor Degree with major in Sales, Marketing, Business Administration;
- At least 5 years of working experience in international and/or major corporations in banking, real-estate, insurance, investment, luxury, hospitality;
- Extensive knowledge of high-end products and solid experience in dealing with VIP & HNWI;
- Excellent communication skills in Vietnamese;
- Good command of English is a must (reading, speaking and writing);
- Ability to learn quickly about many different programs/projects;
- Ability to work both independently and in a team, under high pressure and with tight deadlines;
- Ready to commit and to reach sales targets;
- Analytical, flexible, eager to learn, hard-working, efficient, dynamic, ambitious.

